br.com.henriquewilhelm.orbit

Class PerigeeApogeeCalculator

  • java.lang.Object
    • br.com.henriquewilhelm.orbit.PerigeeApogeeCalculator

  • public class PerigeeApogeeCalculator
extends java.lang.Object
    This program helps those who need to know stage, age, distance and position of the moon along the ecliptic on any date within several thousand years in the past or in the future. The age of the moon day, as well as its visual phase are given. The elliptical longitude moon is calculated, and the corresponding constellation zodiac. The calculated position of the moon based on the Julian day numbers corresponding to the calendar date. The date is set for the valid day of the month.   * http://www.abecedarical.com/zenosamples/zs_lunarphasecalc.html
